t Elizabeth HOMEMAKERS Expo" width="444" height="296" rel="/c/1807/449382.jpg?0" data-height="296" data-lwidth="825" data-lheight="550" class="gflipper-image" align="center">Home is where we laugh, love, cry and make memories.  Our homes tell the story of our lives, it remembers our past, reflects our present through our décor and it is the backdrop for future dreams.  It is a place to be celebrated!The 2018 Port Elizabeth HOMEMAKERS Expo brings a thrilling variety of features and exhibits - sure to tantalise every taste.Sustainable Living The HOMEMAKERS Sustainable Living feature will spotlight “going green” - a holistic look at how we can take a phased approach to living more responsibly. This feature will allow you to explore the world of electric cars, power batteries, giant vegetables and drinking pure sunlight! Join us at our Sustainable Living area where we will educate you on basic elements that will help you reach a status of sustainable prosperity where food, water and energy is something you make in your back yard! Eastern Cape Parks & Tourism Agency (ECPTA) Local is lekker! Need some exciting staycation ideas? Then a visit to the ECPTA emporium is a must.  Not only will you discover some local gems but you stand a chance to win incredible prizes, from a romantic evening to high-intensity getaways. Big kitchen appliance giveaway This year’s Port Elizabeth HOMEMAKERS Expo together with Bosch and Kloppers are giving away high-end Bosch appliances to the value of R50,000! Expo visitors stand a chance to win state-of-the-art products such as a washing machine, tumble dryer, food processors, an oven and so much more! All you have to do to is stop by the competition stand, enter and you could walk away with any one of these fantastic products. We’ll be giving away prizes every day! See you at the expo. CSI - Isivuno training Each year HOMEMAKERS invite a local charity to exhibit at the expo as part of our corporate social investment drive. This year it’s all about Training Trainers - Isivuno provides training and curriculum to preschool teachers working particularly in rural or disadvantaged areas. Deli delights Foodies will not be disappointed with this year’s offering!  Come in and indulge in the exquisite selection of foods and deli delights exclusive to the HOMEMAKERS Expo. Artisan Avenue Take a stroll through the brand-new Artisan Avenue. Here you will find a handpicked selection of local artisans and talented crafters. Design Inspiration presented by the IID The IID, African Institute of the Interior Design Professions, is dedicated to establishing, promoting and maintaining expertise, professionalism, sound business practice and high standard throughout the industry. This year, the IID is bringing Port Elizabeth’s best design talent together on the HOMEMAKERS floor. General info <img src="http://biz-file.com/c/1807/449361.jpg" alt="Port Elizabeth HOMEMAKERS Expo" width="244" height="183">2–5 August 2018 | The Boardwalk Exhibition CentreThursday – Saturday 10am – 7pm, Sunday 10am – 5pmBuy your ticket at the door:  Adults – R50 | Pensioners – R20 | Children under 12 – FreeFor more information phone 041 373 6616 or email pe@homemakers-sa.co.zabRev('brev-af502d4d-bf79-49ce-ae17-2756bb5fc88e', '>a/\<az.oc.as-srekamemoh@ep>"az.oc.as-srekamemoh;46#&ep:otliam"=ferh "knalb_"=tegrat a<')Twitter – @SAHomemakers		Facebook – HOMEMAKERSonlineInstagram – @homemakers_expo	Hashtag: #hmexpoMedia Johandie SlabbertHead of Communication & Marketingjohandie@homemakers-sa.co.zabRev('brev-804f2f30-b95e-45ad-a627-bdc712e6437b', '>a/\<az.oc.as-srekamemoh@eidnahoj>"az.oc.as-srekamemoh;46#&eidnahoj:otliam"=ferh "knalb_"=tegrat a<')084 5678 277 | 086 111 4663